          <p>SECTION 2--AMONG WHAT PERSONS PARTITION
CAN BE SUED FOR
Art. 1307. Â Partition between heirs and legatees.
A partition may be sued for by any heirs, testamentary or ab intestato .
It can also be sued for by any universal legatee or legatee under an universal title, and even by a particular legatee, when a thing has been bequeathed to him in common with one or more persons.</p>
